        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-08-11 09:03:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\n(28 comments)\n\nFirst batch of comments + general design question.\n\nHow is the project supposed to be used in runtime? I would suggest refactoring the project into two modules - library (holding logic related to creating/distributing charts) and application module (with logic related to parsing command line args etc.). That would instantly show any issues that could arise later when trying to use it in some other application e.g. runtimeAPI (I'm not sure where it's going to be implemented.)\n\nAlso consider adding some unit tests for single classes.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
